                  <div class="page-header">
            <h1 class="title">Depth of Field</h1>
          </div>
        
        
        
              </div>

      <div id="content" class="main-content">
        
<div class="l-cf-onecol l-panel" >
  <div class="panel-pane pane-views-panes pane-term-info-panel-pane-1" >
  
      
  
  <div class="view view-term-info view-id-term_info view-display-id-panel_pane_1 view-dom-id-70c7a5bb33bad19a124c294a47070c33">
        
  
  
      <div class="content view-content">
        <div class="clearfix">
      
  <span class="views-field views-field-field-common-system-photo">        <span class="field-content visual-box"><img src="https://www.chinafile.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/assets/images/section/system/study_partner_-_jin_siliu.jpg?itok=WlHvVZsc" width="620" height="414" alt="" /></span>  </span>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-description">        <div class="field-content"><p><span>The Depth of Field column highlights the new and newsworthy photojournalism published in Chinese media by Chinese photographers. For each column, Yan Cong, Ye Ming, and David M. Barreda choose one image from each featured body of work, describe the project, and provide a link to the original piece.</span></p>
</div>  </div>  
  <span class="views-field views-field-field-system-photo-credit">    <span class="views-label views-label-field-system-photo-credit">Photo credit: </span>    <span class="field-content photo-credit">Jin Silu—Tencent “Living” Channel</span>  </span>  </div>
    </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
</div>
  
